Exercise 4.21.  Amazingly, Louis's intuition in exercise 4.20 is correct. It is indeed
 possible to specify recursive procedures without using letrec (or even define), 
although the method for accomplishing this is much more subtle than Louis imagined. 
The following expression computes 10 factorial by applying a recursive factorial procedure:27

((lambda (n)
   ((lambda (fact)
      (fact fact n))
    (lambda (ft k)
      (if (= k 1)
          1
          (* k (ft ft (- k 1)))))))
 10)

